> Is there any idea about this error?
> Thanks a lot!!

I assume you already installed the onnxruntime_gpu_tensorrt-1.0.0-cp36-cp36m-linux_aarch64.whl
using python3 -m pip install onnxruntime_gpu_tensorrt-1.0.0-cp36-cp36m-linux_aarch64.whl ?

Also, you should not run python3 from your onnxruntime source directory.

the error you showed
> >>> import onnxruntime
> Traceback (most recent call last):
>   File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
>   File "/home/nvidia/agxssd512/github/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/__init__.py", line 12, in <module>

suggests that you are running python3 from /home/nvidia/agxssd512/github/onnxruntime
if you import onnxruntime from that directory it will try to look for the python module from that source directory.

cd to a different directory. and if your pip install was successful, it will load the onnxruntime module from the correctly installed location.

issue.title: Build onnxruntime-tensorRT  on Jetson Xavier failed

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
I am trying to build onnxruntime use tensorRT on Jetson Xavier, refer to 
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2684#issuecomment-568548387

**Urgency**
Using SDK Manager4.3 to install CUDA,cuDNN and tensorRT

**System information**
    * Linux Ubuntu 18.04):
    * Name:           NVIDIA Jetson Xavier                                                                                                          
    * Jetpack:        4.3 
    * GPU-Arch:       7.5
  - Libraries:
    * CUDA:           10.0.326
    * cuDNN:          7.6.3.28-1+cuda10.0
    * TensorRT:       6.0.1.10-1+cuda10.0
 
**To Reproduce**
- follow the step as https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2684#issuecomment-568548387
- git clone --recursive https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime
- cd onnxruntime
- git checkout b783805
- export CUDACXX="/usr/local/cuda/bin/nvcc"
- Modify  tools/ci_build/build.py
    - "-Donnxruntime_DEV_MODE=" + ("OFF" if args.android else "ON"),
    + "-Donnxruntime_DEV_MODE=" + ("OFF" if args.android else "OFF"),
- Modify cmake/CMakeLists.txt
    -  set(CMAKE_CUDA_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CUDA_FLAGS} -gencode=arch=compute_50,code=sm_50") # M series
    +  set(CMAKE_CUDA_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CUDA_FLAGS} -gencode=arch=compute_75,code=sm_75") # Jetson support
- ./build.sh --config Release --update --build --build_wheel --use_tensorrt --cuda_home /usr/local/cuda --cudnn_home /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu --tensorrt_home /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu --parallel
